 Invoke with test payload\n452:   - Verify response\n453:   - File: `sdk-python/tests/test_integration.py`\n454:   - Verify: Agent invocation works\n455: \n456: ---\n457: \n458: ## Phase 8: Code Quality ✓\n459: \n460: - [x] **T8.1** Add docstrings to all public classes\n461:   - Document purpose, attributes\n462:   - File: All client files\n463:   - Verify: `help()` displays correctly\n464: \n465: - [x] **T8.2** Add docstrings to all public methods\n466:   - Document parameters with types\n467:   - Document return values\n468:   - Document exceptions\n469:   - File: All client files\n470:   - Verify: Complete API documentation\n471: \n472: - [x] **T8.3** Add type hints to all functions\n473:   - Use `typing` module for complex types\n474:   - File: All source files\n475:   - Verify: mypy passes\n476: \n477: - [x] **T8.4** Run mypy type checking\n478:   - Command: `mypy sdk-python/agentcube/`\n479:   - Fix all type errors\n480:   - Verify: No mypy errors\n481: \n482: - [x] **T8.5** Run ruff/flake8 linting\n483:   - Command: `ruff check sdk-python/agentcube/`\n484:   - Fix all lint errors\n485:   - Verify: No lint errors\n486: \n487: - [x] **T8.6** Run pytest with coverage\n488:   - Command: `pytest --cov=agentcube sdk-python/tests/`\n489:   - Verify coverage >= 80%\n490:   - Verify: All methods tested\n491: \n492: ---\n493: \n494: ## Phase 9: Examples & Documentation ✓\n495: \n496: - [x] **T9.1** Create `examples/basic_usage.py`\n497:   - Show `CodeInterpreterClient` with `with` statement\n498:   - Demonstrate `execute_command()`, `run_code()`\n499:   - Show file operations\n500:   - File: `sdk-python/examples/basic_usage.py`\n501:   - Verify: Example is runnable\n502: \n503: - [x] **T9.2** Create `examples/agent_runtime_usage.py`\n504:   - Show `AgentRuntimeClient` with `with` statement\n505:   - Demonstrate `invoke()`\n506:   - File: `sdk-python/examples/agent_runtime_usage.py`\n507:   - Verify: Example is runnable\n508: \n509: - [x] **T9.3** Create `scripts/e2e_picod_test.py`\n510:   - End-to-end test with live environment\n511:   - Test command execution, code execution, file ops\n512:   - Return exit code 0 on success\n513:   - File: `sdk-python/scripts/e2e_picod_test.py`\n514:   - Verify: Script is executable\n515: \n516: - [x] **T9.4** Create `README.md`\n517:   - Installation instructions\n518:   - Quick start examples\n519:   - API overview\n520:   - Environment variables\n521:   - File: `sdk-python/README.md`\n522:   - Verify: Clear documentation\n523: \n524: ---\n525: \n526: ## Acceptance Criteria\n527: \n528: 1. ✅ `CodeInterpreterClient` creates session via control plane when `session_id` not provided\n529: 2. ✅ Context manager `__exit__` calls `stop()`, deletes session, closes HTTP sessions\n530: 3. ✅ `execute_command()` returns stdout on success\n531: 4. ✅ `CommandExecutionError` raised with `exit_code`, `stderr` on non-zero exit\n532: 5. ✅ File operations (`write_file`, `upload_file`, `download_file`, `list_files`) functional\n533: 6. ✅ Router URL validation: `ValueError` if both arg and `ROUTER_URL` missing\n534: 7. ✅ Session header uses lowercase `x-agentcube-session-id`\n535: 8. ✅ Read timeout buffer (+2.0s) applied to `execute_command()`\n536: 9. ✅ `AgentRuntimeClient` bootstraps session ID via GET invocation endpoint\n537: 10. ✅ `AgentRuntimeClient.invoke()` raises `ValueError` if session_id not initialized\n538: 11. ✅ Control plane handles 404 as idempotent success on delete\n539: 12. ✅ Data plane init failure triggers session cleanup and re-raise\n540: 13. ✅ Package installs via `pip install .`\n541: 14. ✅ Imports work: `from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient, AgentRuntimeClient`\n542: 15. ✅ Unit tests cover all clients and error cases (>= 80% coverage)\n543: 16. ✅ Integration tests pass in live environment\n544: 17. ✅ Type hints pass mypy validation\n545: 18. ✅ Code passes ruff/flake8 linting\n546: 19. ✅ Examples provided and runnable\n547: 20. ✅ README documents installation and usage\n548: \n549: ---\n550: \n551: **Notes:**\n552: - Stage ST-3 marked complete: all clients and tests implemented\n553: - Session header naming: uses lowercase `x-agentcube-session-id` throughout\n554: - Timeout handling: read timeout gets +2.0s buffer to avoid premature `ReadTimeout`\n555: - Exception usage: `SessionError` and `DataPlaneError` defined but not raised by core clients (reserved for future use)\n556: - Distributed configuration: no single `Configuration` class; each client resolves own settings\n557: \n558: (End of file)\n\n(End of file - total 558 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-027 — SDK CodeInterpreterClient Tasks\n\n**Module:** sdk-python  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n**Stage:** ST-3 (completed)\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: Package Structure & Exceptions ✓\n\n- [x] **T1.1** Create `agentcube/__init__.py`\n  - Import `CodeInterpreterClient` from `code_interpreter`\n  - Import `AgentRuntimeClient` from `agent_runtime`\n  - Define `__all__ = [\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]`\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/__init__.py`\n  - Verify: `from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient, AgentRuntimeClient` works\n\n- [x] **T1.2** Create `agentcube/exceptions.py`\n  - Define `AgentCubeError(Exception)` base class","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-027/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775876431797,"end":1775876431846}}}}
